            Literature on Cognition
        </h1>

        <p class="out-bottom-large u-text-center">
            Here’s the entire UX literature on <b>Cognition</b> by
            the Interaction Design Foundation, collated in one place:
        </p>

        
        
        
        <h2 class="heading heading--subSectionHeading">
            All literature
        </h2>

        
        <div class="wrapper col-md-2 out-top-none">
                                                <div>
                        <a href="/literature/article/emotion-and-design" title="Emotion and Design">

    <div class="card js-card card--article  card--mediumArticle   ">
        <div class="card__inner">
            <div class="card__header" data-title="Read article">
                <img                         data-src="https://public-media.interaction-design.org/images/ux-daily/article_130940_hero_5954eb440688c5.80521902.jpg"
                                          alt="Emotion and Design">
            </div>
            <div class="card__contents">
                <h2 class="card__title js-cardTitle truncate-3">Emotion and Design</h2>
                <p class="card__copy truncate-2 ">
                    Factors specific to the things we use in our everyday lives influence how we feel when we are using them. It is, therefore, the role of designers to both understand how we are affected by the products they design, and how they can be developed to (on a small scale) improve the associated user experience, and (on a much grander scale) improve our...
                </p>

                <ul class="card__copy inlineList inlineList--withSeparator u-text-condensed u-text-uppercase sm:hide">
                    <li>111 shares</li>
                    <li>3 months ago</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</a>
